    "scoredNote": "Merino's ultrafine, low-lanolin fiber gives it one of the cleanest hazard bases of any animal fiber, which lands it near 90, high in the green band. Non-superwash, RWS-certified merino sits at the top of that; the chlorine-Hercosett superwash finish and its AOX byproducts are the main thing that pulls a given piece down.",
