      "What can reach your skin is separate: processing residue that was not fully rinsed out, azo dyes, and the same formaldehyde-based wrinkle-resistant finishes used on cotton and linen. Those bother sensitive skin, most on cheap, uncertified pieces. The regenerated fiber itself is rarely the wearer's main risk. The dye or finish added after it usually is."
